text: Dichodactylus is a genus of Japanese funnel weavers first described by K. I. Okumura in 2017. ==Species== it contains four species: *Dichodactylus inabaensis (Arita, 1974) — Japan *Dichodactylus satoi (Nishikawa, 2003) — Japan *Dichodactylus shinshuensis Okumura, 2017 — Japan *Dichodactylus tarumii (Arita, 1976) — Japan ==References== ==External links== Category:Agelenidae Category:Araneomorphae genera
title: Dichodactylus
